ource_uri"=>"https://www.eventbriteapi.com/v3/events/14950366950/", "name"=>{"text"=>"Barbican Kilo Mid-Cycle Sprint", "html"=>"Barbican Kilo Mid-Cycle Sprint"}, "description"=>{"text"=>"This is a three day sprint for contributors of the incubated OpenStack Barbican project.", "html"=>"<P>This is a three day sprint for contributors of the incubated OpenStack Barbican project.</P>"}, "logo"=>{"id"=>"11935043", "url"=>"http://cdn.evbuc.com/images/11935043/78447784269/1/logo.png"}, "id"=>"14950366950", "url"=>"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/barbican-kilo-mid-cycle-sprint-tickets-14950366950?aff=ebapi", "logo_url"=>"http://cdn.evbuc.com/images/11935043/78447784269/1/logo.png", "start"=>{"timezone"=>"America/Chicago", "local"=>"2015-02-16T09:00:00", "utc"=>"2015-02-16T15:00:00Z"}, "end"=>{"timezone"=>"America/Chicago", "local"=>"2015-02-18T17:00:00", "utc"=>"2015-02-18T23:00:00Z"}, "created"=>"2014-12-15T22:00:38Z", "changed"=>"2014-12-16T17:50:22Z", "capacity"=>25, "status"=>"live", "currency"=>nil, "online_event"=>nil, "organizer_id"=>"7826675890", "venue_id"=>"9386508", "category_id"=>"102", "subcategory_id"=>"2999", "format_id"=>"100", "organizer"=>{"description"=>nil, "logo"=>nil, "resource_uri"=>"https://www.eventbriteapi.com/v3/organizers/7826675890/", "id"=>"7826675890", "name"=>"Barbican Team at Rackspace", "url"=>"http://www.eventbrite.com/o/barbican-team-at-rackspace-7826675890", "num_past_events"=>0, "num_future_events"=>1}, "venue"=>{"address"=>{"address_1"=>"701 Brazos Street", "address_2"=>"Suite 1601", "city"=>"Austin", "region"=>"TX", "postal_code"=>"78701", "country"=>"US", "latitude"=>"30.2686057", "longitude"=>"-97.7404689"}, "resource_uri"=>"https://www.eventbriteapi.com/v3/venues/9386508/", "id"=>"9386508", "name"=>"Capital Factory", "lvalue proposition\n\n\n\n\nExperiment Design with Metrics\n\n\n\n\nHow Product Discovery + Agile Delivery can be structured at your company\n\n\n  \nWhat People are Saying \nHow to create new products and services that deliver value to consumers is not guesswork, nor a risky leap of faith. Product development is a highly efficient process, of which, Erin has complete command. Rarely have I had the privilege to work with someone who possesses her clarity of thought; insight without idle opinion; action steps without wasted effort. Although we had been students of lean startup and agile development for quite some time, Erin quickly helped my startup team to synthesize and apply what we'd learned to move our business forward rapidly. Her cheerful, humble demeanor belies a level of entrepreneurial understanding that few can achieve in an entire career.\n \n\nWho Should Attend \nAnyone making decisions on Product or Feature direction or helping others do it well. You're title might be Product Manager, Product Owner, Development Manager, Team Lead, Interaction Designer or Agile Coach.  \nPreparation  \nYou will want to have enough knowledge of Product/Feature direction at your company. This workshop is a \"working session\" where you will have the opportunity to use these new approaches on your actual product. Coming with a team mate or another person from your company to collaborate with is highly recommended in order to maximize the benefits of this workshop. Call us for group rate discounts: (512) 298-2835 xt. 2. \n  \n\nWorkshop Facilitator \nErin Beierwaltes \nErin Beierwaltes counts herself lucky to have found a passion in the agile and organizational cultural movement. \nThrough a mix of system theories, cultural principles and business practices, Erin partners with businesses to find the right balance of product, process and people, to create a responsive and adaptive learning organization. \nErin has been working on organizational development for over 10 years, working with established Product companies and startups, to adopt “just enough” formal approaches to support high paced growth and change. She believes strongly in addressing the combination of product discovery (figuring out what to build), process (how to set up processes to build high quality products quickly), and people (how to create a great culture) to reach organizational level agility. \nIf you don’t find her someplace consumed in organizational culture, then due to her wanderlust, it might be because she temporarily took a break to partake in interesting cultural adventures like, learning to be a mahout (elephant driver) or visiting a monkey training camp. \n\nNotes \n\nGroup pricing is available. Please call to inquire #512-298-2835.\n \nSave $200 off when you attend both this course and the Kanban Foundations workshop on April 2nd. Enter discount code LeanCombo when you sign up for the Kanban Foundations Workshop. Please note the locations are different.", "html"=>"<H3><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large;\">Lean Product Course Description</SPAN></H3>\r\n<P><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px; font-family: symbol;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font: 13px/normal arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">With innovation moving faster than ever, new products and ideas are hitting the market everyday. Unfortunately, most of these products, features and ideas are failing to engage or delight customers, leaving companies with budgets at risk and worse out of business. Agile helped solve the \"how to ship it on time with higher quality\" problems that came from traditional product development, but did not as effectively answer \"how do we ship the RIGHT product?\". \"How do we find Product/Market fit and even more importantly, how do we continue it?\"</SPAN><BR STYLE=\"font: 13px/normal arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"><BR STYLE=\"font: 13px/normal arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font: 13px/normal arial, sans-serif; color: #222222; text-transform: none; text-indent: 0px; letter-spacing: normal; word-spacing: 0px; white-space: normal; font-size-adjust: none; font-stretch: normal; background-color: #ffffff; -webkit-text-stroke-width: 0px;\">Join us in this one day intensive crash course in Product Discovery. Product Discovery brings Product Management the missing process and approach to validating features for Agile Delivery. Learn how to find and solve real customer needs and problems instead of just their demands or your assumptions. See ho
at is <STRONG>Product Discovery</STRONG>? What is <STRONG>Product Discovery</STRONG></SPAN></LI>\r\n</UL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\">How to <STRONG>define</STRONG> the right opportunities</SPAN></LI>\r\n</UL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\"><STRONG>Identify</STRONG> and validate the customer value proposition</SPAN></LI>\r\n</UL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\"><STRONG>Experiment</STRONG> Design with Metrics</SPAN></LI>\r\n</UL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<UL>\r\n<LI><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\">How <STRONG>Product Discovery</STRONG> + Agile Delivery can be structured at your company</SPAN></LI>\r\n</UL>\r\n</UL>\r\n<P> </P>\r\n<H2><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large;\">What People are Saying</SPAN></H2>\r\n<DIV STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">How to create new products and services that deliver value to consumers is not guesswork, nor a risky leap of faith. Product development is a highly efficient process, of which, Erin has complete command. Rarely have I had the privilege to work with someone who possesses her clarity of thought; insight without idle opinion; action steps without wasted effort. Although we had been students of lean startup and agile development for quite some time, Erin quickly helped my startup team to synthesize and apply what we'd learned to move our business forward rapidly. Her cheerful, humble demeanor belies a level of entrepreneurial understanding that few can achieve in an entire career.</SPAN></DIV>\r\n<DIV STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\"> </DIV>\r\n<DIV STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\">\r\n<H2><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large;\">Who Should Attend</SPAN></H2>\r\n<P><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">Anyone making decisions on Product or Feature direction or helping others do it well. You're title might be Product Manager, Product Owner, Development Manager, Team Lead, Interaction Designer or Agile Coach. </SPAN></P>\r\n<H2><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large; font-family: verdana, geneva;\">Preparation<SPAN STYLE=\"line-height: 1.6em;\"> </SPAN></SPAN></H2>\r\n<P><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">You will want to have enough knowledge of Product/Feature direction at your company. This workshop is a \"working session\" where you will have the opportunity to use these new approaches on your actual product. Coming with a team mate or another person from your company to collaborate with is highly recommended in order to maximize the benefits of this workshop. Call us for group rate discounts: (512) 298-2835 xt. 2.</SPAN></P>\r\n<P> </P>\r\n</DIV>\r\n<H2><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large;\">Workshop Facilitator</SPAN></H2>\r\n<P><STRONG><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 12pt; font-family: Helvetica, sans-serif;\">Erin Beierwaltes</SPAN></STRONG></P>\r\n<P STYLE=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; visibility: visible; color: #0a0a0a; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"background-color: #ffffff;\"><IMG STYLE=\"float: right;\" TITLE=\"Erin Beierwaltes\" SRC=\"https://cdn.evbuc.com/eventlogos/30122585/lpperinbeierwaltes600x900200x300.jpg\" ALT=\"Erin Beierwaltes\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva;\">Erin Beierwaltes counts herself lucky to have found a passion in the agile and organizational cultural movement.</SPAN></SPAN></P>\r\n<P STYLE=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; visibility: visible; color: #0a0a0a; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; background-color: #ffffff;\">Through a mix of system theories, cultural principles and business practices, Erin partners with businesses to find the right balance of product, process and people, to create a responsive and adaptive learning organization.</SPAN></P>\r\n<P STYLE=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; visibility: visible; color: #0a0a0a; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; background-color: #ffffff;\">Erin has been working on organizational development for over 10 years, working with established Product companies and startups, to adopt “just enough” formal approaches to support high paced growth and change. She believes strongly in addressing the combination of product discovery (figuring out what to build), process (how to set up processes to build high quality products quickly), and people (how to create a great culture) to reach organizational level agility.</SPAN></P>\r\n<P STYLE=\"margin: 0px 0px 20px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; font-family: Helvetica, Arial, Helvetica, Tahoma, sans-serif; font-size: 14px; font-stretch: inherit; line-height: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; text-rendering: optimizelegibility; visibility: visible; color: #0a0a0a; -webkit-font-smoothing: antialiased !important;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-family: verdana, geneva; background-color: #ffffff;\">If you don’t find her someplace consumed in organizational culture, then due to her wanderlust, it might be because she temporarily took a break to partake in interesting cultural adventures like, learning to be a mahout (elephant driver) or visiting a monkey training camp.</SPAN></P>\r\n<DIV>\r\n<H2><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: large;\">Notes</SPAN></H2>\r\n</DIV>\r\n<DIV><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px; font-family: verdana, geneva;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\">Group pricing is available. Please call to inquire #<A HREF=\"\" TARGET=\"_blank\" REL=\"nofollow\">512-298-2835</A>.</SPAN></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<DIV><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px; font-family: verdana, geneva;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\"><BR></SPAN></SPAN></DIV>\r\n<DIV><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px; font-family: verdana, geneva;\"><SPAN STYLE=\"font-size: 13px;\">Save $200 off when you attend both this course and the Kanban Foundations workshop on April 2nd. Enter discount code <STRONG>LeanCombo</STRONG> when you sign up for the Kanban Foundations Workshop. Please note the locations are different.</SPAN></SPAN></DIV>"}, "logo"=>{"id"=>"12250807", "url"=>"http://cdn.evbuc.com/images/12250807/30333443095/1/logo.jpg"}, "id"=>"15556908131", "url"=>"http://www.eventbrite.com/e/lean-product-discovery-workshop-tickets-15556908131?aff=ebapi", "logo_url"=>"http://cdn.evbuc.com/images/12250807/30333443095/1/logo.
